иг._сказ."/><biblScope>37</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>ba-di-ʼrwagæs wæd!</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>поверь!</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>believe!</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 129</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>osæj dær ba ʼragæs æj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>женщина поверила</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>a woman believed</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>5%l10%l</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>kæmi mi barwagæs adtæjdæ!</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>где мне было поверить!</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>how was I supposed to believe!</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 42</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>kænæd di ærwagæs, kænʒænæj dæmæ eris</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>будь уверена, она будет с тобой спорить</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>be sure, she will argue with you</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/><biblScope>99</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Начальная дигорская группа %iærw%i- восходит обычно к %ivr%i-: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærwæz"/> из *%ivraza%i-, %iærwæd%i (и. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_iræd"/>) из *%ivrata%i; %iærwagæs%i могло получиться из %ivṛ%i- + %iākas-%i „казаться (%iākas%i-) верным (%ivṛ%i-)“, „принять за верное“. Ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kæsyn"/> в значении ‘казаться’, а для первой части — <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wyrnyn"/> ‘верить’, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <w>вера</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="goh"><lang/> <w>wār</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/> <w>verus</w></mentioned>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">The initial digor group %iærw%i- usually traces back to %ivr%i-:<ref type="xr" target="#entry_ærwæz"/> from *%ivraza%i-, %iærwæd%i (Iron <ref type="xr" target="#entry_iræd"/>) from *%ivrata%i; %iærwagæs%i could have been derived from %ivṛ%i- + %iākas-%i "to seem (%iākas%i-) true (%ivṛ%i-)", "to take something for a right thing". Compare <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kæsyn"/> in the meaning ‘to seem’, and as for the first part — <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wyrnyn"/> ‘believe’, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <w>vera</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="goh"><lang/> <w>wār</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/> <w>verus</w></mentioned>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>